Guimarães (1971) recognized the former Zeliini as a New World tribe containing 10 genera:
Diaugia Perty, 1833
;
Huascarodexia Townsend, 1919
;
Ophirodexia Townsend, 1911
;
Opsozelia Townsend, 1919
;
Taperamyia Townsend, 1935
;
Tromodesiana Townsend, 1931
;
Tromodesiopsis Townsend, 1927
;
Ushpayacua Townsend, 1928
;
Yahuarmayoia Townsend, 1927
; and
Zelia Robineau-Desvoidy, 1830
. An 11th genus was added later by Guimarães himself: the monotypic genus
Neozelia Guimarães, 1975
. No further taxonomic study of Zeliini took place after Townsend and Guimarães until new studies provided better taxonomic stability and improved the knowledge of some genera:

1) Nihei & Pavarini (2011) provided a redescription of
Diaugia angusta Perty, 1833
;

